column3: It would be nice to get a deterministic build of qt too, but I'd say if just bitcoin is deterministic building from the same qt, someone do a qt build and release that for everyone to use for 0.5.\n
I didn't know that the qt build was not deterministic yet. I'll give it a try.\n
I just cherry-picked all but the last commit.\n

I had some hex-editor fun and found out that the qt build-nondeterminism is caused by some process adding random (too far apart to be timestamps) 8-character hex codes before function names:

```
-00054760  31 36 37 42 37 41 37 38  31 30 50 72 6f 63 65 73  |167B7A7810Proces|
+00054760  45 41 42 45 39 45 33 44  31 30 50 72 6f 63 65 73  |EABE9E3D10Proces|

-000547b0  30 30 5f 31 36 37 42 37  4

Nice detective work!  Quick update from me:  my house still has no power, so I'm working from my gitian-capable laptop; I'm fetching/compiling dependencies now for the win32 gitian build. I made lots of progress on a Mac build, but all of that work is sitting on my main machine in my powerless house...\n
